# Vercel Deployment Configuration

## Environment Variables

Add these environment variables in the Vercel dashboard under Project Settings â†’ Environment Variables:

### All Environments

```
TURSO_DATABASE_URL=<your-turso-database-url>
TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=<your-turso-auth-token>
JWT_SECRET=<generate-a-secure-random-string>
NODE_ENV=production
```

### How to Get Turso Credentials

1. Sign up at https://turso.tech
2. Create a new database
3. Get the database URL: `turso db show <db-name> --url`
4. Get the auth token: `turso db tokens create <db-name>`

### Generate JWT Secret

Run this command to generate a secure JWT secret:
```bash
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

## Deployment Commands

### Deploy with Vercel CLI

```bash
# Install Vercel CLI globally
npm install -g vercel

# Login to Vercel
vercel login

# Deploy (preview)
vercel

# Deploy to production
vercel --prod
```

### Set Environment Variables via CLI

```bash
vercel env add TURSO_DATABASE_URL production
vercel env add TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN production
vercel env add JWT_SECRET production
vercel env add NODE_ENV production
```
